First off, I would like to make this clear, this is by no means a Frankstein AR-15.
This project has started off as a new Colt SP6940 Military specification rifle. I then sold the the upper of that rifle so that I may fund for the BCM Bravo Company upper, since have a cold hammer forged barrel was very appealing to me. Being that it is cold hammer forged, the barrel's durability is stronger and maintains its accuracy even when the barrel reaches a certain temperature that a normal barrel could not, however I kept the Colt bolt carrier group as hearing it is probably the best in the commercial/military/consumer market that does not include high end custom builders such as Noveske, Daniel Defense, or LaRue. Having still felt incomplete in my build, as far as ergonomics and unique features, I installed a Knight's Armament quad rail with integrated front flip up sight and it is aesthetically and functionally awesome! There are more accessories listed below and you can see in the pictures yourselves.

I have fired 60 rounds through this rifle. 
Bought 100 rounds for it to sight it in and have not taken it out since. 
2 of those 5 boxes were not fired and are included with this sale. 

As I realize that my urge to have something and to customize it, I feel that it is my time to move on to a different project, that doesn't have to exclusively be rifles. It was particularly amusing, but it is time for me to move on and put my efforts into something else to tinker with. 

I don't necessarily need a rifle, it has been a safe queen; I just end up putting more and more money into after seeing and knowing what else can I do to it. Time to move on before, I don't have cash for Christmas.

postcontent:
You are looking at a Custom, RealTree ™ Camo, deep concealment holster/garment similar to Smart Carry ™  and Thunderwear ™.  Due to the nature of camp patterns, I cannot guarantee the exact same finish as in the picture, but it will be RealTree ™. 

Why pay $20-30 MORE for their product if you don't even know it will work for you? You can own this one for far less. If, after trying it and finding out how well it works, you want a more expensive one, at least you'll be confident it's for you. BUT, I'm confident this one will work well if you like this style of carry.


This holster can be used ambidextrously and can accomodate an addtional magazine. Additionally, it incorporates an extra pocket where you can keep your ID, passport or cash. If you visit someplace where pickpockets or muggers are prevalent, this garment could be invaluable. Let the bad guy have your decoy wallet while your main documents and currency remain safe.

The holster is light weight and comfortable for the style. There is extra padding on the back to avoid any rubbing or hot spots. But, it is not bulky and will not print with normal fitting garments. I have worn mine for years and never been "made."
